HEADWORD: Besotted
<hw>Be*sot"ted</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Made sottish, senseless, or
infatuated; characterized by drunken stupidity, or by infatuation;
stupefied.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Besotted</xex> devotion.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Sir W.
Scott.</au> -- <wordforms><wf>Be*sot"ted*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Be*sot"ted*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Besottingly</ent>⟦br⟧
